                       "message":  "MENUREGISTRY-PLAYMENU-A3: add the Play menu (Play/Pause/Stop/Step) via MenuRegistry\n\nThird beat of the menu-breadth arc (A1 File #291, A2 Edit #295). Pure menu/UI\nwiring -- the PIE path is ALREADY runtime-wired through EditorShell::handle_button;\nthis connects the menu\u0027s Commands to it via the existing host-\u003eshell FIFO. NO new\naction, NO new runtime capability.\n\neditor-egui-host (crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs):\n- add PLAY_MENU_EXTENSION_POINT = \"editor.main_menu.play\".\n- build_main_menu_entries() now returns a 3-tuple (file, edit, play): declares the\n  play point, registers Play/Pause/Stop/Step as STATIC MenuEntrys (ids\n  play.start/pause/stop/step), resolves once (one registry, all three points),\n  projects the third list.\n- add play_menu_entries field; new() destructures + stores it; render() paints a\n  third menu_button(\"Play\").\n- 2 new tests (registry resolves Play/Pause/Stop/Step in order; round-trips through\n  the handoff FIFO in order).\n\neditor-shell (crates/editor-shell/src/render_path.rs):\n- drain_and_route_menu_commands routes Command::PlayStart/PlayPause/PlayStop/\n  PlayStep -\u003e handle_button(ToolbarButtonId::Play/Pause/Stop/Step) via a small\n  private route_play_button helper that SWALLOWS the benign invalid-state\n  PlayStateError. Static menu items can be clicked in a state where the transition\n  is a no-op (e.g. Stop while Editing); handle_button returns Err BEFORE mutating,\n  so the swallow is safe. Mirrors the Space/Escape swallow in\n  handle_playback_command; logged at debug (normal user behaviour, not an error).\n\neditor-shell tests (crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/tests.rs):\n- mod menu_routing: menu_play_start_command_starts_pie (Editing-\u003ePlaying);\n  menu_play_pause_step_stop_round_trip_via_pie (all 4 commands: Pause-\u003ePaused, Step\n  stays Paused, Stop-\u003eEditing); menu_play_stop_while_editing_is_a_swallowed_noop.\n  Updated the menu_unrouted_command_is_noop comment (A2 -\u003e A3 routed set).\n\nCommand -\u003e ToolbarButtonId: PlayStart-\u003ePlay, PlayPause-\u003ePause, PlayStop-\u003eStop,\nPlayStep-\u003eStep. No menu item for FrameStep (no Command variant).\n\nv0 ships 4 STATIC items; a dynamic Play\u003c-\u003ePause toggle label needs the deferred\nper-frame re-resolve. No Cargo.toml change (no new crate edge -- editor-egui-host\nand editor-shell already dep editor-ui; editor-shell owns ToolbarButtonId). Stale\nmenu rustdoc/comments widened \"File + Edit\" -\u003e \"File + Edit + Play\" where they\ndescribe the menu set.\n\nDocs (Status/HANDOFF/BASELINE/change) reconcile forward in a follow-up dispatch\n(MENUARC-DOC-RECONCILE-A3), per the established A1-\u003eA2 pattern (code PR, then a\nseparate doc-reconcile PR referencing the merged SHA). This diverges from this\ndispatch\u0027s TASK acceptance (which scoped docs in) in favour of the repo\u0027s\ndemonstrated split.\n\nVerification: cargo check + nightly fmt clean (both crates); \u0026 .ai\\dispatch.verify.ps1\n-\u003e VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (RUST_TEST_THREADS=2).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
