                       "message":  "MENUREGISTRY-PLAYMENU-A3: widen File+Edit menu-set rustdoc to File+Edit+Play (Codex review)\n\nCodex review (NEEDS_CORRECTION) on #297: the A3 PR added Play to the host-\u003eshell\nmenu FIFO but several source rustdoc/comments still described the menu set as\nFile/Edit-only -- the same current-state prose-drift class #296 cleaned up.\nDocs-only fix; no logic change.\n\nWidened every now-narrow menu-set framing in editor-egui-host:\n- handoff.rs: \"pushes a Command when a File or Edit menu item is activated\" -\u003e\n  \"File, Edit, or Play\".\n- lib.rs (build-fn doc): \"single source of truth for both menus\u0027\" -\u003e \"all three\n  menus\u0027\".\n- lib.rs (menu_command_handoff field doc): \"the File + Edit menu bars enqueue\" -\u003e\n  \"File + Edit + Play\".\n- lib.rs (play_menu_entries field doc): \"produced ... alongside the File + Edit\n  entries\" -\u003e \"produced ... (one registry resolves all three points)\".\n- lib.rs (menu_command_handoff accessor doc): \"The File + Edit menu bars drawn by\n  render enqueue\" -\u003e \"File + Edit + Play\".\n- lib.rs (render comment): \"The File + Edit menu bars push onto it\" -\u003e \"File +\n  Edit + Play\".\n\nTwo of these (handoff.rs and the field doc) WRAP across lines, which is why the\nEXEC\u0027s single-line sweep missed them; this pass used a complete MULTILINE sweep --\nevery \"File + Edit\" now reads \"File + Edit + Play\", and no \"File or Edit\" / \"both\nmenus\" / \"two menus\" remains in editor-egui-host or editor-shell.\n\ncargo check + nightly fmt clean. Docs-only (the .rs logic is byte-identical to the\ngate-passed 03edd65; the lints read source structure, not prose).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
